**Sec. 70401. Enhancement of Employer-Provided Child Care Credit.**

This section increases the employer-provided child care credit, raising the amount of qualified child care expenditures taken into account from 25% to 40% (50% for eligible small businesses). The maximum credit amount is raised to $500,000 ($600,000 for eligible small businesses), with annual inflation adjustments starting in 2027. The credit is also extended to third-party intermediaries and jointly owned or operated child care facilities.

**Sec. 70402. Enhancement of Adoption Credit.**

This section modifies the adoption credit by making a portion of it refundable. The credit amount is adjusted for inflation, and the refundable portion is not subject to carryforward. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70403. Recognizing Indian Tribal Governments for Purposes of Determining Whether a Child Has Special Needs for Purposes of the Adoption Credit.**

This section amends the adoption credit to include Indian tribal governments in determining whether a child has special needs. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70404. Enhancement of the Dependent Care Assistance Program.**

This section increases the limit on the dependent care assistance program from $5,000 to $7,500. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70405. Enhancement of Child and Dependent Care Tax Credit.**

This section modifies the child and dependent care tax credit by adjusting the applicable percentage based on the taxpayer's adjusted gross income. The credit is reduced for higher-income taxpayers. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70411. Tax Credit for Contributions of Individuals to Scholarship Granting Organizations.**

This section introduces a new tax credit for individual contributions to scholarship granting organizations, allowing a credit of up to $1,700 per year. The credit is reduced by any state credit for similar contributions. The amendments apply to taxable years ending after December 31, 2026.

**Sec. 70412. Exclusion for Employer Payments of Student Loans.**

This section extends the exclusion for employer payments of student loans, removing the current expiration date of January 1, 2026. The exclusion amount is adjusted for inflation starting in 2027. The amendments apply to payments made after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70413. Additional Expenses Treated as Qualified Higher Education Expenses for Purposes of 529 Accounts.**

This section expands the types of expenses that can be covered by 529 accounts to include elementary and secondary education expenses, such as tuition, books, and tutoring. The maximum distribution limit is increased to $20,000. The amendments apply to distributions made after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70414. Certain Postsecondary Credentialing Expenses Treated as Qualified Higher Education Expenses for Purposes of 529 Accounts.**

This section allows 529 accounts to cover certain postsecondary credentialing expenses, including tuition, fees, and continuing education costs for maintaining credentials. The amendments apply to distributions made after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70415. Modification of Excise Tax on Investment Income of Certain Private Colleges and Universities.**

This section modifies the excise tax on investment income for private colleges and universities, increasing the tax rate based on the student-adjusted endowment. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70416. Expanding Application of Tax on Excess Compensation Within Tax-Exempt Organizations.**

This section extends the tax on excess compensation within tax-exempt organizations to cover employees of such organizations who were employees after December 31, 2016. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70421. Permanent Renewal and Enhancement of Opportunity Zones.**

This section makes permanent the opportunity zone program, with decennial designations and enhanced rules for investments. The amendments apply to areas designated after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70422. Permanent Enhancement of Low-Income Housing Tax Credit.**

This section increases the low-income housing tax credit ceiling and modifies the tax-exempt bond financing requirement. The amendments apply to calendar years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70423. Permanent Extension of New Markets Tax Credit.**

This section extends the new markets tax credit indefinitely and allows for carryover of unused limitations. The amendments apply to calendar years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70424. Permanent and Expanded Reinstatement of Partial Deduction for Charitable Contributions of Individuals Who Do Not Elect to Itemize.**

This section increases the partial deduction for charitable contributions of individuals who do not elect to itemize from $300 to $1,000. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70425. 0.5 Percent Floor on Deduction of Contributions Made by Individuals.**

This section introduces a 0.5 percent floor on charitable contributions made by individuals, with certain exceptions. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70426. 1-Percent Floor on Deduction of Charitable Contributions Made by Corporations.**

This section introduces a 1 percent floor on charitable contributions made by corporations, with a 10 percent cap. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70427. Permanent Increase in Limitation on Cover Over of Tax on Distilled Spirits.**

This section increases the limitation on cover over of tax on distilled spirits from $12.50 to $13.25. The amendments apply to distilled spirits brought into the United States after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70428. Nonprofit Community Development Activities in Remote Native Villages.**

This section allows nonprofit entities to engage in fisheries-related activities in remote native villages without losing their tax-exempt status. The amendments apply to activities conducted during the existence of the western Alaska community development quota program.

**Sec. 70429. Adjustment of Charitable Deduction for Certain Expenses Incurred in Support of Native Alaskan Subsistence Whaling.**

This section increases the charitable deduction limit for expenses incurred in support of Native Alaskan subsistence whaling from $10,000 to $50,000. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70430. Exception to Percentage of Completion Method of Accounting for Certain Residential Construction Contracts.**

This section allows residential construction contractors to use the completed contract method of accounting for contracts that are not home construction contracts. The amendments apply to contracts entered into in taxable years beginning after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70431. Expansion of Qualified Small Business Stock Gain Exclusion.**

This section increases the gain exclusion for qualified small business stock from 50% to 100% for stock held for at least 5 years, with a phased increase for stock held for 3 to 5 years. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70432. Repeal of Revision to De Minimis Rules for Third Party Network Transactions.**

This section reinstates the de minimis exception for third party network transactions, requiring reporting only if the amount exceeds $20,000 and the number of transactions exceeds 200. The amendments apply to calendar years beginning after December 31, 2024.

**Sec. 70433. Increase in Threshold for Requiring Information Reporting with Respect to Certain Payees.**

This section increases the threshold for information reporting with respect to certain payees from $600 to $2,000. The amendments apply to payments made after December 31, 2025.

**Sec. 70434. Treatment of Certain Qualified Sound Recording Productions.**

This section allows qualified sound recording productions to be treated as qualified film or television productions for tax purposes, with certain limitations. The amendments apply to productions commencing in taxable years ending after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70435. Exclusion of Interest on Loans Secured by Rural or Agricultural Real Property.**

This section excludes 25% of the interest on loans secured by rural or agricultural real property from gross income. The amendments apply to taxable years ending after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70436. Reduction of Transfer and Manufacturing Taxes for Certain Devices.**

This section eliminates the transfer and manufacturing taxes for firearms, except for machineguns and destructive devices. The amendments apply to calendar quarters beginning more than 90 days after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70437. Treatment of Capital Gains from the Sale of Certain Farmland Property.**

This section allows taxpayers to pay tax on capital gains from the sale of certain farmland property in installments over four years. The amendments apply to sales or exchanges in taxable years beginning after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70438. Extension of Rules for Treatment of Certain Disaster-Related Personal Casualty Losses.**

This section extends the rules for treating certain disaster-related personal casualty losses, applying the provisions of the Taxpayer Certainty and Disaster Tax Relief Act of 2020. The amendments apply to losses incurred after the enactment of the Act.

**Sec. 70439. Restoration of Taxable REIT Subsidiary Asset Test.**

This section restores the taxable REIT subsidiary asset test, increasing the percentage of assets that must be held in qualifying assets from 20% to 25%. The amendments apply to taxable years beginning after December 31, 2025. [end of text]


